content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 7 blocks total
- It has 3 layers:
  * Bottom layer: 3 vertical orange cylindrical pillars
  * Middle layer: 2 horizontal yellow rectangular blocks
  * Top layer: 1 vertical orange cylindrical pillar with 1 yellow semi-circular cap

Spatial Relationships:
- The three orange pillars form a U-shape at the base
- Two yellow rectangular blocks are placed horizontally across the top of the pillars
- A single orange pillar rises from the center of the yellow blocks
- A yellow semi-circular cap sits on top of the uppermost orange pillar

Required Blocks from Dictionary:
- Orange vertical cylinders (Block #7) x 4
- Yellow horizontal rectangles (Block #1 or #2) x 2
- Yellow semi-circular cap (Block #10 or #11) x 1

Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 7
    Step2: Move block with index 7
    Step3: Move block with index 7
    Step4: Move block with index 1
    Step5: Move block with index 2
    Step6: Move block with index 7
    Step7: Move block with index 10
}

The assembly sequence starts from the bottom up, first placing the three support pillars, then the horizontal platform blocks, followed by the top pillar and finally the decorative cap.
